{
  "texts": [
    "It will also be useful to consider a partial reduction of the representation variety R Θ, obtained in the following way (see the last paragraph of [BY20]): Instead of considering a framing of the full fibre V b, let us just choose a point i l ∈ ⟨q l ⟩ b and a framing of V 0 b (i l) for each active circle ⟨q l ⟩, which we will refer to as a minimal framing.",
    "Forgetting the framings of all other graded pieces of the fibre V b amounts to acting on R Θ with a subgroup",
    "Concretely, this action can be used to bring the pieces ρ ⟨q l ⟩ of the formal monodromy ρ(∂) in (3.3) to the form (2)",
    "where the first index corresponds to the point i l (cf. equation (1)).",
    "Definition 3.11."
  ]
}